latestPosts.caption:
Last year, when @taylorswift announced her international dates for @taylorerastour in Singapore, that was our initial destination.
But with hundreds of thousands of people already ahead of us on the waiting list for the tickets, we didn’t stand a chance and we were queued out. 

Honestly, London wasn’t even on our radar, but when we received an email invite to apply for the tickets at Wembley Stadium, for her last European leg.
It felt like our only shot, at what could maybe be a once-in-a-lifetime experience.

I’ll never forget that early morning when the tickets were just about to go live at a “GMT time zone” and @lizzansalldhana and I were glued to our laptops, holding our breaths, patiently waiting in a queue with millions of other Swifties, from all over Britain and USA, praying and hoping just to get our tickets before it’s sold out again. 

The chances were super slim, and it felt like a long shot— I mean, what could even be the possibility, really? 

But with a HUGE STROKE of LUCK and with the blessings of the international credit card gods, WE GOT THEMMMM AND HOW!!! 🥹😅💃🏻

From planning the entire trip to finally attending the Eras Tour, to this specific evening, seeing Taylor so up close, giving her all for three hours straight without any breaks will be etched in my CORE MEMORY FOREVER! 

My respect for @taylorswift as an ARTIST is through the roof. 
She left us in absolute awe, giving 90,000 people goosebumps the entire time! What a super star! 

Sometimes, universe sure does have much bigger plans for you, than the ones you make for yourself.✨✨✨

And I obviously channelled my inner “Reputation Era” IFYKYK😅💅💁🏻‍♀️

ENDLESS GRATITUDE ONLY🧿🧿❤️
